comments: There were definite patterns in the study. Most of the words only had slight variations between the colours although that could sometimes be difficult to keep track of because it was so slight. I did not use paper to take notes, I tried to learn them through memory. I found the circles the easiest to remember because it seemed like they were all written the same way. I found the gafyco words the most difficult and I couldn't get a hang of the variations in the spelling for the different colours.
